body:
Character development

So, I’ve been rewatching all 7 seasons of game of thrones just recently and I was hit with one of the most amazing character developments of all times.

Jaime Lannister…

He started as a real prick. A spoiled, arrogant brat. But throughout the series, he grew to be one of my most beloved characters in the entire show. He survived until now, is dead loyal to his brother, who everyone in his family just despises. He took care of Brienne and saved her life multiple times. And finnaly he saw the wrong ways of Cersei, the woman he loved above everyone else, and chose to do the right thing for the greater good and leave.

This man has one of the most amazing character development since this word exists and I love this guy!!!

summary: (this post might contain possible spoilers for Got season 8 since i’m focusing on friki’s leaks. also please forgive my broken...
body:
my theories on episode 2

(this post might contain possible spoilers for Got season 8 since i’m focusing on friki’s leaks. also please forgive my broken english, it’s not my first language.)

things i think will happen in season 2 :

1) Cersei is going to either have a miscarriage or discover she’s not actually pregnant.

{ Cersei: Will the king and I have children?

Maggy: Oh, aye. Six-and-ten for him, and three for you. }

according to maggy the frog’s prophecy cersei is not going to have more than 3 children. so her being in pregnant have shocked most of us but i don’t think that she’s ever give birth. we see her drinking wine in the trailer so maybe that’s after she had her miscarriage & realized the truth of maggy’s prochecy (you can also see some tears in her eyes aw).

as for the fales pregnancy, well cersei is kinda crazy rn so i won’t put it past her to fake being pregnant to get sympathy from other people (tyrion). there’s a chance that she didn’t know it herself & thought that having a belly means she’s with a child (i haven’t read most of the books but i heard that she gained mire & more weight throughout them). either way she will not be kept away from drinking wine for much longer.

2) jaime arrives in winterfell.

according to friki jaime will not appear in episode 1. therefore he will probably finally show up in the north in the 2nd ep. i think that he gives his speech (about fighting for the living) after he’s confronted by dany. bran’s an omniscient god now so things are cool between them, and the other starklings (particularly arya) will be wary at first but brienne will likely defend him. dany however will not trust him since he betrayed her father & they fought in season 7.

speaking of dany…

3) jon will reveal his parentage to daenerys.

(screaming in dance of the dragons 2.0)

i talked about this particular theory in an earlier post & someone questioned if jon would risk doing it himself but i think that he believes that she deserves to hear it from him & not from someone else.

friki said that jon was told in episode 1 by bran & sam, he will should be finished moping around by this point. i don’t think crypts scene we saw from the trailer was AFTER dany knew the truth but BEFORE . the reveal will not go over well for her, she will not trust jon & will think that he was using her obvious attraction for him to gain her dragons and armies to take the iron throne (after defeating the others ofc). they will have an argument that will end in her taking her dragons and armies to attack KL (it has been foreshadowed enough). varys will change his alliance to the newest targaryen in town.

for some reason i don’t think that the unsullied & will go idk. maybe greyworm stays & missandei goes with dany. either way that romance is doomed in gw is definitely dying in battle.

edit: i forgot to add that i think the shot of sansa looking worried in trailer is her (+arya ??) watching dany leave winterfell.

4) the golden company attacks winterfell.

{ i will not set foot in king’s landing while cersei lannister is queen. they want another stark prisoner, they can come and take me.}

- sansa in 7x06

so many people have analyzed the trailer & they pointed out that team winterfell is shown fighting against other humans. this is were the GC comes in, i don’t know if it’s in this episode or in ep1 but cersei negotiate with them to siege WF. it’s probably after hearing the news of dany abandoning them (*cough* from tyrion *cough*). the part were arya’s running around all bloody is after they’ve kidnapped sansa & killed some of the people hiding in the crypts. they’re trying to kidnappe her two (she reminds me here of when the waif was chasing her).

a set pictures of jon & cersei in KL have accidentally been leaked a while back. i also remember someone mentioning that she saw kit, lena & sophie there. in the new EW article i think one of d&d (i forgot to take a screenshot) said that an important scene has been leaked via a stone & i believe it was this scene of jon in some episode later going to “rescue” sansa.

5) the episode ends with the arrival of WW.

we don’t actually see the battle of winterfell until episode 3 but we will see the army of wights looking at winterfell & everyone preparing for the coming battle.

they don’t have dragons, they’re worn out thanks to GC & they will definitely lose.

other thoughts :

friki said that dany taught jon how to train his dragon™️ in episode 1. could jon form a connection to rhaegal (the dragon named after his biological father & the one friki said he will ride)? maybe rhaegal chooses to stay with jon or comes back later in episode 3 so they’re more even with the white walkers? it would certainly be interesting.

so.. what do you guys think? feel free to agree/disagree with me!
